{
  "stem": "24268.4",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "When you felt so close with people who loved you so much, that made a little bit easier, the life, to struggle-- the hard times, this hardship.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Where we went, we went first to-- and we-- we registered to United States.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But then we had some difficulty in Bremerhaven, I think, and then we went to Canada.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In Canada, something happened what my husband didn't like, and then we went to United States.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we came to United States.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We helped-- my husband helped a lot of people to get through-- the consul and doctor, whatever.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He was very helpful, always been.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He sacrificed all his life always for others, being in camp or without, even up till the last minute, even today.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It-- even after the war, we got-- we constantly-- whenever we-- every year, practically, we went to Israel.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "There was practically nothing in Israel-- was no hotels, no airport.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We had nothing, just the beginning.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "That was right after the war.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And there was a difficult time for-- for them as well as for us, and we tried to share whatever we had.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We send them extra thing always with the suitcases.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My brother used to say, what do you carry in this?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I say, there was all full of clothes, and the bedspread, and sheets, which are quite heavy, and money, whatever we could.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Because I could-- I got letters.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I still have.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I cannot hear the cry of the children.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "How could I eat if I know this kind of letter?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I get something like this from people that I didn't even know, but I think as a human being you cannot just ignore pain like this.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And they were our people.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
